{"scenarioDescription":"\n  <ul class=\"exoplanets-navigation-menu\">\n  <li><button href=\"#system\">System</button>\n  <li><button href=\"#GJ 581\">Star</button>\n  <li><button href=\"#GJ 581-b\">b</button></li> <li><button href=\"#GJ 581-c\">c</button></li> <li><button href=\"#GJ 581-e\">e</button></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1 id=\"system\">The GJ 581 Exoplanetary System</h1>\n  <p>The GJ 581 system contains 3 exoplanets. It is located 20.54 light years away from the solar system.</p>\n    <div class=\"celestial-object-wrapper\" id=\"GJ 581\">\n  <section>\n  <h2>Star</h2>\n  <div class=\"size-comparison-wrapper\">\n  <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 100px; height: 100px; background-color: rgb(255, 242.3979365143785, 230.54885609599933);\">\n    <label>Sun</label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 33px; height: 33px; background-color: rgb(255, 189.53325005981566, 134.94095806884098)\">\n<label>GJ 581</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n  </section>\n  <table cellspacing=\"0\">\n  <tr>\n    <td>Mass</td>\n    <td>0.31 solar masses</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Radius</td>\n    <td>0.33 solar radiae</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Temperature</td>\n    <td>3396 kelvin</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Stellar Metallicity</td>\n    <td>-0.088 decimal exponent</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Age</td>\n    <td>4.3 billion years</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n     \n    <div class=\"celestial-object-wrapper\" id=\"GJ 581-b\">\n      <section>\n        <h2>GJ 581-b</h2>\n        <p>    At more than 10 Earth masses, GJ 581 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune.  </p>\n        <div class=\"size-comparison-wrapper\">\n          <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 10px; height: 10px;\">\n            <label>Earth</label>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 41.1px; 